         <div type="edition" xml:lang="kaw-Latn" rendition="class:38769 maturity:83211">
            <p><lb n="1"/><g type="spiralR"/> <num value="924">924</num> təvəkniṁ hnū binənərakən· da<lb break="no" 
                n="2"/>məl· <abbr>samgat·</abbr> lucəm pu ghək·
			<lb n="3"/>saṅ apañji təpət i mananəm·
			<lb n="4"/>boddhi variṅi<supplied reason="lost">n</supplied>· <g type="spiralR"/>
             </p>
         </div>
         <!-- <div type="apparatus"/> -->
         <div type="translation" resp="part:argr">
 	        <p><supplied reason="subaudible">In Śaka year</supplied> 924 was when the road was put right. It was the work of the offial opf Lucəm <supplied reason="subaudible">called</supplied> <foreign>pu</foreign> Ghək, who had the courtly name Təpət, for planting a sacred fig tree.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p/>
         </div>
        <div type="bibliography">
           <p>First edited by H. Kern in <bibl><ptr target="bib:Holle1883_03"/></bibl> (republished as <bibl><ptr target="bib:Kern1917_16"/></bibl>). Edited again by Damais (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:Damais1955_01"/></bibl>), who used the OD photos 2692–2694. For a complete bibliography, see <bibl><ptr target="bib:TitiSurtiNastiti+al2025_01"/></bibl>.</p>
